{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d1a346dd-1b47-44de-bf4a-c80b29e6c459","content":"Here's the architecture and plan for your RAG-based Q&A feature:\n\n---\n\n## Architecture Overview\n\n```\n┌─────────────┐       ┌──────────────────┐       ┌────────────────┐\n│  Docs/*.md  │──────▶│  Ingestion       │──────▶│  Vector Store  │\n│  (source)   │       │  (chunk+embed)   │       │  (in-memory)   │\n└─────────────┘       └──────────────────┘       └───────┬────────┘\n                                                         │\n┌─────────────┐       ┌──────────────────┐               │\n│  User Query │──────▶│  /api/ask        │──── search ───┘\n│  (question) │       │  (retrieve+gen)  │\n└─────────────┘       └──────────────────┘\n```\n\n---\n\n## Components\n\n### 1. Document Ingestion Pipeline\n- **Loader** — reads all `Docs/*.md` files at startup (or via `POST /api/ingest`)\n- **Chunker** — splits each markdown file into overlapping chunks (~300–500 tokens, ~100-token overlap) using heading/paragraph boundaries\n- **Embedder** — generates vector embeddings per chunk via OpenAI `text-embedding-3-small` (through `Microsoft.Extensions.AI`)\n- **Store** — persists chunks + vectors in an in-memory vector store (upgradeable to Qdrant/Postgres+pgvector later)\n\n### 2. Query Endpoint (`POST /api/ask`)\n- Accepts `{ \"question\": \"...\" }`\n- Embeds the question → cosine-similarity search → retrieves top-K chunks (K=3–5)\n- Constructs a grounded prompt: system message + retrieved chunks + user question\n- Calls an LLM (GPT-4o via `Microsoft.Extensions.AI`) to generate the answer\n- Returns `{ \"answer\": \"...\", \"sources\": [...] }` with chunk provenance\n\n### 3. Recommended Packages\n| Package | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|\n| `Microsoft.Extensions.AI` | Unified AI abstractions (embeddings + chat) |\n| `Microsoft.Extensions.AI.OpenAI` | OpenAI provider |\n| `Microsoft.Extensions.VectorData.Abstractions` | Vector store abstraction |\n| `Microsoft.SemanticKernel.Connectors.InMemory` | In-memory vector store (dev/small scale) |\n\n### 4. Project Structure (proposed)\n```\nProductQA/\n├── Docs/                    # existing markdown sources\n├── Services/\n│   ├── DocumentChunker.cs   # markdown → chunks\n│   ├── IngestionService.cs  # orchestrates load+embed+store\n│   └── QAService.cs         # retrieve+generate\n├── Models/\n│   ├── DocumentChunk.cs     # chunk record with vector\n│   └── AskRequest/Response  # API DTOs\n├── Controllers/\n│   └── AskController.cs     # POST /api/ask, POST /api/ingest\n├── Program.cs               # DI registration\n└── appsettings.json         # API keys, model config\n```\n\n### 5. Key Design Decisions\n- **Chunking strategy**: split on markdown headings first, then paragraph boundaries, with overlap to preserve context across boundaries\n- **In-memory store**: simplest start; swap to a persistent vector DB via the abstraction layer when scaling\n- **Grounding**: the LLM prompt explicitly instructs \"only answer from provided context\" to reduce hallucination\n- **Startup ingestion**: `IHostedService` ingests docs on app start; `/api/ingest` allows re-triggering\n\n---\n\nWant me to implement this?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ca0e07ad-2c0b-442a-83d5-4bfe26aa7484","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Now I have a good understanding of the project. It's a minimal .NET 10 Web API with some product documentation markdown files. The user wants a plan and architecture for adding RAG-based Q&A. Let me provide a clear architecture and plan without writing any code.","outputTokens":999,"requestId":"5C34:22ED17:61E796:712A6E:69FAA507"},"id":"c7af2f87-1e21-45eb-9c2d-cd8f84e66cf4","timestamp":"2026-05-06T02:19:08.136Z","parentId":"df42b8bc-497d-4e9f-87b9-4e4e4d4ee51d"}
